-- European Stocks Decline as H&M, Vedanta, Mitie Slump; BP, Rolls-Royce Gain
-- B y   W i l l   H a d f i e l d
-- 2010-09-29T08:14:18Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-09-29/european-stocks-decline-as-h-m-vedanta-mitie-slump-bp-rolls-royce-gain.html
European stocks retreated, falling
for a third consecutive day.  The benchmark Stoxx Europe 600 Index slid 0.6 percent to
260.84 at 9:12 a.m. in London, after earlier gaining as much as
0.7 percent.  Hennes & Mauritz AB sank 6 percent to 243.40 kronor after
Europe’s second-largest clothing retailer reported third-quarter
net income that missed analysts’ estimates.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Will Hadfield at 
 whadfield@bloomberg.net  